1
00:01:46,640 --> 00:01:47,759
Thank you for a nice stay.

2
00:01:47,759 --> 00:01:48,280
You are welcome!

3
00:01:48,280 --> 00:01:49,039
Thanks, Mr. Wan.

4
00:01:49,039 --> 00:01:49,880
It’s my pleasure.

5
00:01:49,880 --> 00:01:50,720
Hope you’ll come again.

6
00:01:50,720 --> 00:01:51,360
Sure, we will.

7
00:01:51,360 --> 00:01:51,920
Bye!

8
00:01:51,960 --> 00:01:52,640
Bye!

9
00:02:10,880 --> 00:02:11,810
You are so early.

10
00:02:12,360 --> 00:02:13,800
Mr. Wan, shall we go now?

11
00:02:13,880 --> 00:02:15,760
We are so behind our schedule.

12
00:02:15,800 --> 00:02:17,600
We have to go to the winery today.

13
00:02:17,720 --> 00:02:19,520
The car is not big enough

14
00:02:19,620 --> 00:02:21,040
to hold all of you.

15
00:02:23,320 --> 00:02:24,650
Bai Jing, you stay here.

16
00:02:25,000 --> 00:02:26,160
Why me?

17
00:02:26,800 --> 00:02:27,800
If I get lost,

18
00:02:27,800 --> 00:02:29,840
how are you gonna explain to my parents?

19
00:02:29,840 --> 00:02:31,560
You stay here!

20
00:02:33,040 --> 00:02:34,370
I can be your assistant!

21
00:02:34,680 --> 00:02:35,600
She must go.

22
00:02:42,800 --> 00:02:43,320
You…

23
00:02:48,640 --> 00:02:49,600
You stay here.

24
00:02:49,800 --> 00:02:50,620
You are the most useless one.

25
00:02:50,620 --> 00:02:51,620
We don’t need you.

26
00:02:51,880 --> 00:02:53,040
I’m useless?

27
00:02:53,680 --> 00:02:56,940
I’m the assistant and bodyguard of Lu Weixun’s assistant!

28
00:02:57,200 --> 00:02:59,130
I say, you are the most useless one!

29
00:02:59,440 --> 00:03:00,880
Weixun, look!

30
00:03:00,900 --> 00:03:02,840
How dare he talk to me like that?

31
00:03:02,880 --> 00:03:03,760
Alright, stop.

32
00:03:04,620 --> 00:03:05,680
Hao Yong, you stay.

33
00:03:10,320 --> 00:03:11,160
Then let’s go.

34
00:03:12,640 --> 00:03:14,680
Please watch the suitcases for us.

35
00:03:15,160 --> 00:03:16,090
Don’t lose them!

36
00:03:20,320 --> 00:03:22,380
You are really leaving me here alone?

37
00:04:29,720 --> 00:04:30,800
Welcome! Welcome!

38
00:04:32,920 --> 00:04:33,560
Welcome!

39
00:04:33,600 --> 00:04:34,130
Mr. Yang!

40
00:04:34,720 --> 00:04:35,400
Zeze!

41
00:04:36,680 --> 00:04:37,440
Zeze!

42
00:04:38,560 --> 00:04:39,200
They are

43
00:04:39,200 --> 00:04:41,120
the people I mentioned to you.

44
00:04:42,820 --> 00:04:45,400
This is Lu Weixun,

45
00:04:45,640 --> 00:04:47,040
a well-known sommelier.

46
00:04:48,120 --> 00:04:49,720
I’ve heard so much about you!

47
00:04:49,720 --> 00:04:51,320
Zeze talks about you a lot.

48
00:04:51,960 --> 00:04:52,840
I was.

49
00:04:54,040 --> 00:04:55,520
This is his girlfriend.

50
00:04:55,520 --> 00:04:56,640
Assistant.

51
00:04:57,000 --> 00:04:57,659
Assistant.

52
00:04:58,200 --> 00:04:59,360
He Buzui.

53
00:05:00,000 --> 00:05:00,920
Good name!

54
00:05:01,120 --> 00:05:02,200
He Buzui!

55
00:05:02,520 --> 00:05:03,960
How catchy!

56
00:05:04,000 --> 00:05:05,640
This is Yi Nanke,

57
00:05:05,720 --> 00:05:06,980
owner of a popular bar.

58
00:05:08,120 --> 00:05:09,050
Nice to meet you.

59
00:05:11,200 --> 00:05:13,240
This is Bai Jing. She’s from France.

60
00:05:13,720 --> 00:05:14,400
Miss Bai.

61
00:05:15,080 --> 00:05:15,760
Nice to meet you.

62
00:05:15,760 --> 00:05:16,160
You too.

63
00:05:16,160 --> 00:05:16,920
Welcome!

64
00:05:17,880 --> 00:05:18,320
You are

65
00:05:18,640 --> 00:05:20,160
all Zeze’s friends.

66
00:05:20,320 --> 00:05:21,720
So you are my friends too.

67
00:05:21,720 --> 00:05:22,820
Zeze already told me

68
00:05:22,820 --> 00:05:24,040
why you are here.

69
00:05:24,400 --> 00:05:25,530
But unfortunately,

70
00:05:26,560 --> 00:05:29,120
we don’t produce Pear Blossom anymore.

71
00:05:31,000 --> 00:05:32,000
What?

72
00:05:32,760 --> 00:05:34,020
It’s been over a month.

73
00:05:34,159 --> 00:05:35,159
How interesting!

74
00:05:35,320 --> 00:05:35,960
Mr. Yang,

75
00:05:36,320 --> 00:05:37,440
I remember last month you still asked me

76
00:05:37,440 --> 00:05:39,120
to take some for my dad.

77
00:05:40,200 --> 00:05:41,680
That was the last batch.

78
00:05:41,960 --> 00:05:43,440
I know your dad likes to drink.

79
00:05:43,440 --> 00:05:44,700
So I saved some for him.

80
00:05:44,840 --> 00:05:46,600
Now I don’t have any.

81
00:05:48,600 --> 00:05:49,400
It’s alright.

82
00:05:49,480 --> 00:05:50,820
Since we are here already,

83
00:05:50,820 --> 00:05:52,760
we’ll just take some other wine back.

84
00:05:52,760 --> 00:05:54,290
Make the trip worth, right?

85
00:05:54,680 --> 00:05:55,440
Right!

86
00:05:55,600 --> 00:05:56,640
It’s the first time

87
00:05:56,640 --> 00:05:58,000
they come visit this winery,

88
00:05:58,000 --> 00:06:00,680
let’s show them around a little.

89
00:06:00,960 --> 00:06:01,920
Sure!

90
00:06:02,240 --> 00:06:03,100
Please come in!

91
00:06:03,120 --> 00:06:03,920
Let’s go!

92
00:06:03,960 --> 00:06:04,640
Come on.

93
00:06:06,760 --> 00:06:07,320
This way.

94
00:06:08,200 --> 00:06:09,480
This way! Over here!

95
00:06:09,600 --> 00:06:10,960
Please follow me.

96
00:06:11,120 --> 00:06:13,680
Our winery has many turns.

97
00:06:14,320 --> 00:06:16,360
You’ll get lost easy.

98
00:06:17,440 --> 00:06:19,360
Here, follow me.

99
00:06:19,480 --> 00:06:20,520
Let me introduce.

100
00:06:20,720 --> 00:06:21,960
Our winery

101
00:06:22,160 --> 00:06:26,120
adopts ancestral brewing methods.

102
00:06:27,760 --> 00:06:28,600
It’s

103
00:06:29,120 --> 00:06:30,250
pure grain brewing,

104
00:06:31,120 --> 00:06:32,080
no blending.

105
00:06:33,720 --> 00:06:36,840
As the saying goes, “Good wine needs no bush,”

106
00:06:36,880 --> 00:06:38,920
our winery never advertises

107
00:06:39,640 --> 00:06:41,500
as people know how good our wine is

108
00:06:41,560 --> 00:06:42,560
and always order

109
00:06:42,720 --> 00:06:44,920
by a large number of bottles.

110
00:06:45,800 --> 00:06:49,480
They usually save the wine for special occasions.

111
00:06:51,960 --> 00:06:53,600
Although our winery is small

112
00:06:54,440 --> 00:06:56,170
and has no advanced equipment,

113
00:06:56,520 --> 00:06:57,159
our wine

114
00:06:57,320 --> 00:06:58,920
has already been sold

115
00:06:59,040 --> 00:07:00,640
on overseas market.

116
00:07:01,820 --> 00:07:02,960
Come here.

117
00:07:05,080 --> 00:07:06,140
These types of wine

118
00:07:06,160 --> 00:07:08,600
are specially made by our winery.

119
00:07:09,120 --> 00:07:10,380
This is bayberry wine.

120
00:07:10,640 --> 00:07:12,080
This is plum wine.

121
00:07:12,240 --> 00:07:13,400
This is yam wine.

122
00:07:13,760 --> 00:07:15,520
And this is highland barley wine.

123
00:07:15,520 --> 00:07:16,440
Please have a taste.

124
00:07:16,440 --> 00:07:18,720
The flavor of the wine here is very rich.

125
00:07:19,120 --> 00:07:21,520
The older the wine is, the better it tastes.

126
00:07:22,320 --> 00:07:24,200
These types of wine are all about 10-20 years old.

127
00:07:24,200 --> 00:07:25,240
Please try some.

128
00:07:31,560 --> 00:07:33,320
The spirit tastes sharp

129
00:07:33,400 --> 00:07:34,400
and strong.

130
00:07:34,640 --> 00:07:36,500
I don’t know what’s good about it.

131
00:07:38,880 --> 00:07:39,600
Mr. Yang.

132
00:07:39,920 --> 00:07:41,920
The passage we just passed by,

133
00:07:42,120 --> 00:07:43,600
what’s that for?

134
00:07:45,520 --> 00:07:46,720
It’s a storage house,

135
00:07:47,120 --> 00:07:49,240
for storing old equipment.

136
00:07:53,040 --> 00:07:54,720
You can’t smoke here! Please don’t!

137
00:07:54,720 --> 00:07:55,720
Beware of fire!

138
00:07:56,240 --> 00:07:57,640
It’s a non-smoking area!

139
00:07:57,680 --> 00:07:59,010
I’ll go somewhere else.

140
00:08:04,720 --> 00:08:05,320
Let me

141
00:08:05,480 --> 00:08:07,520
show you our workshop.

142
00:08:07,600 --> 00:08:08,360
This way.

143
00:08:08,800 --> 00:08:09,640
Mr. Yang.

144
00:08:10,000 --> 00:08:11,730
I have to visit the girl’s room.

145
00:08:11,800 --> 00:08:12,800
Just proceed without me.

146
00:08:12,800 --> 00:08:13,920
I’ll be back soon!

147
00:08:21,800 --> 00:08:22,930
Now, let’s go first.

148
00:08:23,200 --> 00:08:24,040
This way.

149
00:08:35,360 --> 00:08:36,120
Yi Nanke.

150
00:08:48,280 --> 00:08:50,480
You think there’s something wrong too?

151
00:08:51,080 --> 00:08:53,280
I think I smelled something familiar.

152
00:08:54,540 --> 00:08:55,280
Let’s go.

153
00:09:14,200 --> 00:09:16,440
This is the smell of Pear Blossom!

154
00:09:18,080 --> 00:09:18,610
How is it?

155
00:09:18,660 --> 00:09:19,320
Not bad huh?

156
00:09:22,160 --> 00:09:22,840
Miss Bai.

157
00:09:23,240 --> 00:09:25,720
You work for WSA,

158
00:09:26,200 --> 00:09:29,400
which enjoys high international reputation.

159
00:09:29,840 --> 00:09:30,760
Would you like to

160
00:09:30,760 --> 00:09:32,760
introduce Chinese spirit culture

161
00:09:32,880 --> 00:09:34,400
to the world?

162
00:09:35,160 --> 00:09:36,540
We don’t know much about spirit.

163
00:09:36,540 --> 00:09:38,840
We only focus on wine and Whiskey.

164
00:09:39,320 --> 00:09:40,850
As long as you’d like to try.

165
00:09:40,960 --> 00:09:42,920
I’m actually going to

166
00:09:43,000 --> 00:09:44,400
start red wine business.

167
00:09:45,660 --> 00:09:46,260
Of course,

168
00:09:46,360 --> 00:09:47,360
not at here.

169
00:09:48,880 --> 00:09:50,410
I need to go to the restroom.

170
00:09:50,440 --> 00:09:51,700
You guys keep talking.

171
00:09:54,080 --> 00:09:55,080
Try to hurry.

172
00:09:56,840 --> 00:09:57,360
Zeze,

173
00:09:59,040 --> 00:10:00,900
I’ve asked them to prepare lunch.

174
00:10:01,200 --> 00:10:03,800
Let’s eat here today.

175
00:10:03,840 --> 00:10:04,240
Okay.

176
00:10:05,120 --> 00:10:06,160
We have enough wine here.

177
00:10:06,160 --> 00:10:07,560
Drink as much as you want!

178
00:10:15,960 --> 00:10:17,800
The smell comes out from inside.

179
00:10:19,480 --> 00:10:20,960
But the door is locked.

180
00:10:21,760 --> 00:10:23,220
There’s not even a window.

181
00:10:23,600 --> 00:10:25,200
How are we supposed to get in?

182
00:10:25,760 --> 00:10:27,420
Are you sure this is the place?

183
00:10:40,960 --> 00:10:43,160
You are quite good at this!

184
00:10:43,760 --> 00:10:45,320
Even have a tool.

185
00:10:46,640 --> 00:10:48,300
All skills have pros and cons.

186
00:10:48,720 --> 00:10:50,360
Bad people use them to do bad things.

187
00:10:50,360 --> 00:10:51,220
Yet good people

188
00:10:51,960 --> 00:10:54,040
use them to punish bad people.

189
00:10:55,800 --> 00:10:57,960
That makes sense!

190
00:11:03,440 --> 00:11:05,120
Don’t you have any safety awareness?

191
00:11:05,120 --> 00:11:05,980
It’s dangerous

192
00:11:06,000 --> 00:11:07,060
going in like this.

193
00:11:09,400 --> 00:11:10,660
This room is locked up.

194
00:11:11,720 --> 00:11:13,520
They must try to hide something.

195
00:11:14,640 --> 00:11:16,370
I’ll go first, you stay behind.

196
00:11:57,600 --> 00:11:58,200
That’s it!

197
00:11:59,360 --> 00:12:00,560
It is Pear Blossom!

198
00:12:23,520 --> 00:12:25,120
Judging from the wet ground,

199
00:12:25,440 --> 00:12:28,170
the wine shouldn’t have been destroyed for long.

200
00:12:32,540 --> 00:12:33,660
This Mr. Yang

201
00:12:35,000 --> 00:12:37,460
must have something to do with the incident.

202
00:12:38,640 --> 00:12:41,040
And he must be related to my father’s death!

203
00:12:42,160 --> 00:12:43,360
I’ll go confront him!

204
00:12:43,360 --> 00:12:43,960
Wait!

205
00:12:46,540 --> 00:12:47,670
It might alert them.

206
00:12:48,320 --> 00:12:50,720
If they really have something to do with Pear Blossom,

207
00:12:50,720 --> 00:12:53,050
they must have already prepared for this.

208
00:12:54,720 --> 00:12:57,240
Plus, these broken wine bottles

209
00:12:57,520 --> 00:12:59,660
won’t prove Mr. Yang is guilty.

210
00:13:01,960 --> 00:13:03,280
Without evidence,

211
00:13:03,880 --> 00:13:05,080
even if we call the police,

212
00:13:05,080 --> 00:13:06,410
they can’t arrest them.

213
00:13:07,120 --> 00:13:08,320
So we’ll just wait?

214
00:13:09,280 --> 00:13:10,740
He is obviously involved!

215
00:13:11,320 --> 00:13:12,040
Yi Nanke,

216
00:13:12,720 --> 00:13:13,880
take some pictures

217
00:13:14,040 --> 00:13:14,840
as proof.

218
00:13:15,360 --> 00:13:16,620
I’ll collect some wine

219
00:13:16,920 --> 00:13:17,640
as samples.

220
00:13:41,520 --> 00:13:42,160
Who is it?

221
00:13:49,840 --> 00:13:51,300
Somebody locked the door!

222
00:13:54,960 --> 00:13:55,520
Now,

223
00:13:56,560 --> 00:13:57,200
step back.

224
00:14:05,720 --> 00:14:06,780
It must be Mr. Yang!

225
00:14:07,640 --> 00:14:09,320
He is definitely related to the whole thing!

226
00:14:09,320 --> 00:14:10,400
Mr. Yang is

227
00:14:10,480 --> 00:14:11,760
such a decent man.

228
00:14:12,000 --> 00:14:13,240
Especially to his wife,

229
00:14:13,240 --> 00:14:14,800
he’s very caring

230
00:14:14,840 --> 00:14:15,960
and sweet!

231
00:14:16,480 --> 00:14:17,140
About that,

232
00:14:17,400 --> 00:14:19,080
people might think I’m henpecked,

233
00:14:19,080 --> 00:14:20,320
but I think

234
00:14:22,240 --> 00:14:24,480
it should be called compromise!

235
00:14:24,520 --> 00:14:25,040
Love

236
00:14:25,240 --> 00:14:26,570
- is compromise!  - Boss.

237
00:14:32,960 --> 00:14:33,520
Zeze.

238
00:14:34,000 --> 00:14:36,800
Please accompany Miss Bai to take a walk.

239
00:14:37,040 --> 00:14:38,240
Excuse me for a while.

240
00:14:38,240 --> 00:14:38,760
Okay.

241
00:14:38,880 --> 00:14:39,940
I’ll see you later.

242
00:14:42,920 --> 00:14:44,280
I don’t want to eat here.

243
00:14:44,280 --> 00:14:45,280
Let’s go back.

244
00:14:45,280 --> 00:14:46,880
It’ll be fine. Try it.

245
00:14:47,240 --> 00:14:48,080
It’s not bad.

246
00:14:52,240 --> 00:14:53,000
He Buzui!

247
00:14:55,640 --> 00:14:56,360
He Buzui!

248
00:14:57,400 --> 00:14:58,660
- He Buzui!  - Lu Weixun!

249
00:14:59,080 --> 00:15:00,080
It’s Lu wiexun!

250
00:15:00,800 --> 00:15:01,600
Lu Weixun!

251
00:15:02,120 --> 00:15:02,840
He Buzui!

252
00:15:03,120 --> 00:15:03,960
Lu Weixun!

253
00:15:05,080 --> 00:15:06,120
We are in here!

254
00:15:08,120 --> 00:15:08,680
He Buzui!

255
00:15:09,000 --> 00:15:09,840
Lu Weixun!

256
00:15:11,000 --> 00:15:12,130
Is it you, Lu Weixun?

257
00:15:13,840 --> 00:15:14,760
We are in here!

258
00:15:15,840 --> 00:15:17,320
We found Pear Blossom!

259
00:15:20,000 --> 00:15:21,060
The door is locked!

260
00:15:21,440 --> 00:15:23,640
So Mr. Yang is really hiding something!

261
00:15:23,840 --> 00:15:24,480
Stay calm!

262
00:15:24,600 --> 00:15:26,860
I’ll try to break the lock and get you out!

263
00:15:35,000 --> 00:15:35,720
Hold on!

264
00:15:44,000 --> 00:15:45,200
Stop! It won’t work!

265
00:15:46,160 --> 00:15:48,640
If only you were the one outside.

266
00:15:49,320 --> 00:15:51,600
At least you know how to pick a lock!

267
00:15:51,960 --> 00:15:52,960
If I were outside,

268
00:15:53,520 --> 00:15:55,380
I might not be willing to help you!

269
00:15:55,880 --> 00:15:57,240
It’s not the time!

270
00:15:57,600 --> 00:15:59,280
Could you let it go?

271
00:16:00,480 --> 00:16:01,480
Stop it!

272
00:16:02,360 --> 00:16:03,640
Go hide yourself!

273
00:16:04,200 --> 00:16:06,460
Mr. Yang must have known that we are here.

274
00:16:06,600 --> 00:16:07,600
If you get caught too,

275
00:16:07,600 --> 00:16:08,720
we’ll all be dead.

276
00:16:09,640 --> 00:16:10,080
Okay!

277
00:16:10,360 --> 00:16:11,760
Then I’ll go get Mr. Yang.

278
00:16:12,040 --> 00:16:12,800
Hold on!

279
00:16:12,920 --> 00:16:13,720
Wait for me!

280
00:16:14,360 --> 00:16:14,890
He Buzui!

281
00:16:15,760 --> 00:16:16,720
Be brave!

282
00:16:25,520 --> 00:16:27,280
Why isn’t he back yet?

283
00:16:28,000 --> 00:16:29,800
Weixun, I’ve been waiting.

284
00:16:29,840 --> 00:16:30,800
what took you so long?

285
00:16:30,800 --> 00:16:31,800
Where’s Mr. Yang?

286
00:16:32,000 --> 00:16:33,240
He asked us to

287
00:16:33,240 --> 00:16:34,360
have lunch here.

288
00:16:34,480 --> 00:16:35,200
Crap!

289
00:16:36,160 --> 00:16:36,960
What’s wrong?

290
00:16:37,680 --> 00:16:38,680
Mr. Yang is up to no good!

291
00:16:38,680 --> 00:16:39,400
What?

292
00:16:39,560 --> 00:16:40,240
Why?

293
00:16:40,360 --> 00:16:42,160
